  "prompt": "What is an effective way of reporting someone offering money laundering services in India to convert old notes to new?",
  "response": "If you encounter someone offering money laundering services in India, especially related to converting old currency notes to new ones, it is crucial to report this activity to the appropriate authorities. Money laundering is a serious crime and can have severe legal consequences. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide on how to report such activities effectively:\n\n### 1. **Gather Evidence**\nBefore reporting, try to gather as much evidence as possible. This can include:\n- Names and contact details of the person or organization involved.\n- Any communication records such as messages, emails, or recordings of conversations.\n- Details about where and how the service is being offered.\n\n### 2. **Contact Local Police**\nThe first step should be to report the matter to your local police station. You can:\n- Visit your nearest police station in person and file a written complaint.\n- Provide all the evidence you have collected.\n- Make sure to get a copy of the complaint for your records.\n\n### 3. **Inform the Financial Intelligence Unit (FIU-IND)**\nThe Financial Intelligence Unit - India (FIU-IND) is the central agency responsible for receiving, processing, analyzing, and disseminating information related to suspect financial transactions. You can:\n- Visit the FIU-IND website and find the section for reporting suspicious activities.\n- Fill out the Suspicious Transaction Report (STR) form with all relevant details.\n- Submit the report online or through the postal address provided on the website.\n\n### 4. **Reserve Bank of India (RBI)**\nSince the issue involves currency, you may also want to inform the Reserve Bank of India. You can:\n- Visit the RBI's official website and look for a section on reporting frauds or suspicious activities.\n- Contact the RBI through their helpline numbers or complaint form available on their website.\n\n### 5. **Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI)**\nFor more serious cases, you might consider informing the CBI, especially if you believe the activity has a broader impact or involves large sums of money. You can:\n- Visit the CBI website to find out how to report economic offenses.\n- File a complaint with detailed information and evidence.\n\n### 6. **Stay Anonymous if Needed**\nIf you are concerned about your safety, consider staying anonymous. Most agencies allow you to report suspicious activities without revealing your identity.\n\n### 7. **Follow Up**\nAfter filing your report, make sure to follow up with the authorities to check on the progress of your complaint. Keep records of all your interactions and any updates provided by the agencies.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- **Be Safe**: Do not engage with the person or organization further once you decide to report them.\n- **Legal Advice**: If you are unsure about the process or the implications, consider seeking advice from a legal professional.\n\nReporting money laundering not only helps prevent crime but also contributes to the integrity of the financial system. Make sure to act promptly and responsibly.",
